cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as morphological annotation and spelling correction in Arabic. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves querying a morphological analyzer for possible analyses. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it utilizes machine learning techniques to assist annotators and improve productivity. Finally, it may also fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it describes a web interface designed to facilitate the annotation process for human annotators.
